Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.53,0:12:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,At 440, you have...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.53,0:12:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Academic medicine at calibration level 440, academic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.29,0:12:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinical medicine calibrates at 445.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That extra five points is significant
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.90,0:12:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're talking a logarithm to the base 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.03,0:13:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So the number of patients who recover
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,with a more holistic approach
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is higher than with academic medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.09,0:13:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, I had the largest psychiatric practice
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.09,0:13:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States, back east, for 25 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.09,0:13:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we saw all the patients
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.09,0:13:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,who made the rounds of academia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.27,0:13:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And what we used was more innovative...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call that kind of medicine?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.27,0:13:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call the word?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.57,0:13:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Alternative medicine or whatever you want to call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.00,0:13:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got a name, whatever the name is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.51,0:13:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,More holistic, yes, holistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.00,0:13:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so with holistic medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and then, of course, academics will poo-poo holistic medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.02,0:13:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.02,0:13:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,acupuncture, this and that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.05,0:13:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But the cure rate is much higher
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.05,0:13:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with the clinical than academic medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.05,0:14:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If academic medicine cured them all,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.05,0:14:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have had any patients to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.05,0:14:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So clinical medicine is more innovative,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.30,0:14:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and we take advantage of the Heisenberg principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.30,0:14:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the cure rate amongst patients...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.30,0:14:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed, because I used to hire a lot of therapists,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.30,0:14:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,psychologists, psychiatrists, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.30,0:14:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,some people had tremendously good results
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with really impossible people,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.30,0:14:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and other people just consistently had bad results.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.50,0:14:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was related, upon investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.50,0:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to the consciousness level of the therapist, the doctor, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.60,0:14:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So a doctor, the true clinical physician,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.51,0:14:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,utilizes everything because his dedication
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.51,0:14:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is to the healing of the patient,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.51,0:14:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve some scientific doctrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.51,0:14:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, the limitation of science is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.51,0:14:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that it becomes a doctrine,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.51,0:14:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes religionized, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.51,0:14:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you say, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.72,0:15:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,do you want to go see an acupuncturist?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.72,0:15:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The person goes, an acupuncturist?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've already told the story of my ulcer,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.75,0:15:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,intractable ulcer that almost killed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.75,0:15:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,perforating into the pancreas, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.87,0:15:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which I had for 25 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.87,0:15:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I saw all the clinical,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.87,0:15:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the academic,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.87,0:15:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the academic medicine, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.87,0:15:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I heard that acupuncture
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.87,0:15:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was first coming into America.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.87,0:15:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It started in Washington, D.C.,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.87,0:15:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've told the story before.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.87,0:15:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to see, I flew down there from New York,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.87,0:15:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,saw this old Chinese, he didn't speak English,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.87,0:15:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remember when he put a needle
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.87,0:15:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,right through this wrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that acupuncture was painless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.87,0:15:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I screamed, and he goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.97,0:15:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,ho, ho, ho, bad ulcer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.00,0:15:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ho, ho, ho, bad ulcer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.00,0:15:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,His diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.54,0:15:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew the diagnosis from the one needle,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.54,0:15:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and from the third treatment on,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.67,0:15:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the truth of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.67,0:15:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I have not had any recurrence
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.67,0:16:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of a chronic recurrent duodenal ulcer,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.67,0:16:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was by a poo-poo treatment, acupuncture.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.74,0:16:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll tell you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.00,0:16:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now that Dr. Kallenbach and I
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.00,0:16:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,were talking about it at lunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these alternative treatments will always work
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.00,0:16:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in a certain percentage of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.00,0:16:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we set up a clinical treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.02,0:16:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or a clinical academic test,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.02,0:16:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,100 patients on this and 100 patients on this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the 100 on the alternative medicine
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.70,0:16:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,are probably not statistically going to do as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.70,0:16:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but within, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.10,0:16:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,if you've got 100 people on alternative medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.10,0:16:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say acupuncture,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say 22% are cured,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.10,0:16:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and let's say with chronic antacids
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.10,0:16:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and antispasmodics, 47%.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.10,0:16:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like one is better
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.10,0:16:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,than the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.10,0:16:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll tell you where the fallacy is,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.10,0:16:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were discussing this at lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.54,0:16:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of a group, there's a subgroup
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.54,0:17:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the cure rate for this treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.54,0:17:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.34,0:17:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of 100 people with an ulcer,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say 27%,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.34,0:17:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if you know who the 27 are,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,pull them out and treat them with acupuncture,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.34,0:17:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a cure rate of 100%
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.34,0:17:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of duodenal ulcers with acupuncture,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.34,0:17:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,if you knew how to pick them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.92,0:17:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Kallenbach and I figured that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see, with our diagnostic technique,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.33,0:17:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,we could screen and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.33,0:17:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,this person would respond to this person,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.33,0:17:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,so we pull out the responders.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.33,0:17:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,For some people, that's going to be 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.33,0:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For some people, all you've got to do
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.00,0:17:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is take wheat and gluten out of their diet
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.00,0:17:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and their schizophrenia disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.00,0:17:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I actually did that many a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.00,0:17:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But which of the crowd are the ones?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.00,0:17:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So statistics lie, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.10,0:17:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When you say only 10% cures,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.10,0:17:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but amongst that 10%,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.10,0:17:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your cure rate was 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.10,0:17:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You got that point, what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:18:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So one other diagnostic tool, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.20,0:18:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way you can discern in your patient subgroup
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.20,0:18:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,who's going to respond to what
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.20,0:18:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and get a very high cure rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.20,0:18:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, alternative medicine, we use everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.20,0:18:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention of the doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.29,0:18:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, you go from doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.29,0:18:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,academic doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.29,0:18:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you go to become a clinician,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.29,0:18:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and then in the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.29,0:18:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,you become a healer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So there are doctors who are in the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have an even higher rate than the others
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.46,0:18:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because the energy they put out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.46,0:18:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is of a healing energy in the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.46,0:18:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So a doctor who calibrates at 520
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.68,0:18:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to have a higher cure rate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.80,0:18:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,than people at 440, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.80,0:18:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.80,0:18:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you want is a doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.06,0:18:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,who's spiritually committed, spiritually oriented,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.06,0:18:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and is dedicated to the recovery of his patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.06,0:18:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And not to his own ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.06,0:18:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can remember making that decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.06,0:18:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The patient sitting there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.06,0:18:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,was I going to use a non-traditional way
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.06,0:19:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and cure this patient,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.06,0:19:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,or am I going to stick with what my colleagues say
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.06,0:19:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and not get laughed at?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.06,0:19:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that instant, I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.06,0:19:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,when I took the oath to be a physician,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.06,0:19:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I promised to God to use my skills
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.06,0:19:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for the benefit of the patients,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.06,0:19:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,not to become popular with my colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.06,0:19:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So in that moment, I made the decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.06,0:19:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, therefore, intention plays such a big part,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the Heisenberg principle
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.76,0:19:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,plays an important part
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.76,0:19:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in the application of science,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.76,0:19:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially clinical science.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.16,0:19:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we were looking at strange things
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.34,0:19:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,like morphic resonance,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.34,0:19:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,morphogenetic fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.34,0:19:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheldrake's morphogenetic fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.34,0:19:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as somewhat aligned with what you hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.34,0:19:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to materialize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.56,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,M-theory was formerly known as string theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.56,0:19:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's arguable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.56,0:19:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In science, it calibrates as 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.64,0:19:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that there's multiple universes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.64,0:20:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates as true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.99,0:20:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian causality principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.99,0:20:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we've pointed out, Sir Isaac Newton's principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.99,0:20:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate at 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.99,0:20:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is really the very center of science,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.99,0:20:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which sees everything in terms of linear causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.04,0:20:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-linear dynamics, you know, at 460.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.04,0:20:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Prayer increases healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.18,0:20:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nuclear fission reaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.18,0:20:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the actuality of nuclear,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.18,0:20:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the nuclear reaction is 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.18,0:20:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.18,0:20:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither good, nor bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.18,0:20:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Nuclear reaction is neither good, nor bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.18,0:20:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the body and the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.18,0:20:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates at 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.18,0:20:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which is neither good, nor bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.18,0:20:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it isn't the nuclear fission,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.18,0:20:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what you do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.47,0:20:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Nuclear fission theory itself is at 455.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.92,0:20:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We did organisms on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.92,0:20:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,parallel universe theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.92,0:20:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum coherence,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:20:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,quantum gravity, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.10,0:21:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the last slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.46,0:21:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.64,0:21:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we on 203?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.27,0:21:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Or 204?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.24,0:21:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is page two of science theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the last one?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.24,0:21:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.24,0:21:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.24,0:21:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to make sure we cover all the things
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.24,0:21:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that we mentioned, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.29,0:21:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.68,0:21:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,we've discussed that many times
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.68,0:21:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Schrodinger equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.68,0:21:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,S matrix theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.68,0:21:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is spiritual experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.68,0:21:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is the consequence of neural activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.68,0:21:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We've checked that in many different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.91,0:21:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Stem cell research, 245.
